President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with the academia, the Nigerian Bar Association and the National Judicial Council on the passing of Prof. David Ijalaye. The president in a condolence message by his spokesman, Mr. Femi Adesina in Abuja on Thursday, noted that the good works of the scholar would continue to speak loud. Buhari commiserated with family, friends and associates of Ijalaye, who devoted his life to the teaching and practice of law, putting in more than 34 years in service before his retirement in 1998. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! The president saluted Ijalaye for devoting the rest of his life to consulting, counselling and service to humanity. Buhari assured that the legacies of the legal luminary would always be preserved, acknowledging that Ijaleye left distinguished results as Dean, Faculty of Law, Deputy Vice-Chancellor and Chairman, Board of Postgraduate Studies of the Obafemi Awolowo University. COVID-19 Vaccine Safe, Umahi Assures Ebonyi Residents Federal Salary Structure Canâ€™t Be Imposed On States- Fayemi Ijalaye was also a Fellow of the Nigeria Institute of Advanced Legal Studies and Fellow of the Nigerian Society of International Law. Buhari prayed that almighty God would receive the soul of the departed and comfort his family. Source (NAN)